cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for tracking living cells in video sequences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes deep learning models such as UNet, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of UNet for extracting spatio-temporal information also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with mitosis detection, which is a subfield of medical imaging, and hence, it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a multi-cell tracking approach, which could also fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
